headline: Powell says 'downside risks to employment appear to have risen,' implying more Fed cuts are possible
summary: Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said Tuesday that the outlook for employment and inflation has not changed much since the central bank's September meeting. He emphasized, however, that "the downside risks to employment appear to have risen."
